HDR-CX7 Highlights
3.2-megapixel ClearVid CMOS sensor The 1/2.9-inch ClearVid CMOS sensor provides stunning detail and clarity with exceptional video (1080 lines of resolution in HD Mode; 530 lines of horizontal resolution in SD Mode) and still image performance (6.1-megapixel). Unlike traditional CCD imagers, CMOS sensors require less power, providing better battery performance.
Switchable HD/SD format recording The HDR-CX7 is capable of recording and playing back both High Definition (HD) and Standard Definition (SD) video recorded on Memory Stick PRO Duo media (sold separately).
x.v.Color Technology x.v.Color technology can capture or display nearly twice as many (1.8x) viewable colors than currently possible. This provides a more accurate and vivid color range, for a more natural, lifelike overall experience.
10x optical/20x digital zoom The optical zoom helps to bring the action close up from far away. In addition, the digital zoom interpolation means that extreme digital zooming is clearer, with less distortion than previous types of digital zoom.
Professional-quality Carl Zeiss Vario- Sonnar T* lens Carl Zeiss lenses have an advanced optical multi-layer coating that offers less glare and flare with increased contrast. This results in vivid image brilliance, true-to-life color saturation and perfect renditions of subtle tones. The additional T* coating on the lens further reduces unwanted glare and flare.
2.7-inch widescreen Hybrid touch-panel Clear Photo LCD Plus display The 2.7-inch 16:9 LCD screen provides excellent viewing clarity with improved resoltuion. The 211K-pixel screen also rotates up to 270 degrees for multiple viewing angles, providing sharp, detailed images for monitoring or playback. The widescreen format makes shooting in 16:9 mode and composing shots even easier.
Smooth slow record By increasing the record rate from 60 fields per second (fps) to 240 fps for 3 seconds allowing you to capture 3 seconds of fast motion and play the video back in 12 seconds. This is great for analyzing a golf swing or a viewing a bird in flight. In addition, record an audio track to narrate what is being seen in the video.
Memory Stick PRO Duo Media slot Capture still images up to 2848 x 2136 resolution, directly onto Memory Stick PRO Duo Media for easy trasfer to PCs for emailing, printing or shairing with other compatible Memory Stick PRO Duo devices.
Dual record While recording video in High Definition you have the ability to capture a 4.6-megapixel still image directly to Memory Stick PRO Duo media.
Super SteadyShot Optical Image Stabilization system An advanced form of Sony's SteadyShot Image Stabilization system that controls an even higher range of shake and vibration frequencies. This optical stabilization system achieves an even higher level of smoothness without degradation of vide like some digital stabilization systems.
Tele Macro function Useful for shooting close up shots, but without having the camcorder casting a shadow on the subject. Images shot in the Tele Macro mode will have the subject properly focused with the background unfocussed so that the subject stands out.
Active Interface Shoe Provides a location directly on the camcorder on which to add optional accessories while providing power and two-way communication to those accessories.
Built-in intelligent flash For added clarity and detail when taking pictures in low-light situations, the built-in flash improves pictures and reduces shadows.
Super NightShot infrared system With Sony's NightShot infrared system, capture video in total darkeness (0 lux) up to 10 feet away. Super NightShot mode automatically adjusts the shutter speed to increase picture brightness and clarity. Color Slow Shutter mode allows you to record in low light situations with full color detail by slowing down the shutter speed.
Scene Selection modes Scene Selection modes make recording easy even when filming in challenging situations. Choose from Beach, Candle, Fireworks, Landscape, Portrait, Sports Lesson, Spotlight, and Sunrise & Sunset.

postcontent: Taurus Millennium G2 9MM Semi Auto PistolDavidsons Lifetime Replace or Repair WarrantyWith its lightweight 22 oz. polymer frame, thin profile, and ramped 3.2 inch barrel, the newly designed Millennium G2 is the ideal concealed carry handgun. Available in two compact models—PT 111 and PT 140—the Millennium G2 features an accessory rail, high-profile sights, an aggressive, textured grip and melted edges for added comfort and easy concealment. Taurus Security System (TSS)sTaurus family of semi-auto pistols now feature the Taurus Security System, which provides instant-ready defense with built-in ability to secure your pistol and make it inoperable at the turn of a key. When the Security System is engaged, the pistol cannot be fired or cocked and the gun's manual safety cannot be disengaged. As with our revolver Security System, the device is part of the firearm and cannot be lost, and the same special Security Key works for both the revolver and pistol Systems (two keys come with each gun). To engage: simply insert the Key into the button on the rear or side of the pistol and rotate one-quarter turn clockwise. This engages the Security System. The manual safety cannot be moved and the trigger cannot be pulled. To disengage: simply rotate the key one-quarter turn back. This releases the Security System, yet leaves the pistol's manual safety in the "safe" position until you are ready to release it yourself and fire the gun.    Loaded Chamber IndicatorTaurus provides a loaded chamber indicator on all new compact, medium and large frame pistols. postcontent:
Bushmaster XM-15 (AR-15) complete upper receiver assembly

- upper-receiver

16in Carbine M4 Type Upper Receiver.
Part No: F1007445
Price: $626.24 [ note: that’s way overpriced in today’s market ]
Currently  Out Of Stock.



also included:

- Mako dual-picatinny mount (installed on the hand guards)
- AR-15 pistol grip
- AR-15 collapsible stock ( commercial spec diameter )
- AR-15 buffer tube ( commercial spec diameter )
— - does not include buffer and buffer spring


Since this is just the upper-receiver assembly, no background check is required (for now), and this can be shipped to other states without going through an FFL dealer.




caveat (short):  If you plan on shooting Russian steel-case ammo (such as “Wolf” or “Tula”), you probably don’t want to buy this upper receiver assembly.  With the post-panic glut of AR-15 parts available, you’ll have no problem finding another one.



caveat (long):  This is from a Bushmaster XM-15 that I bought in November 2008.  I ended up trading this upper-receiver to a friend of mine, which he put on a Bushmaster lower that I had sold him a few years earlier (back when Colorado was still a free state).  At the same time, we also bought several cases of Wolf .223 62 grain hollow-point ammo.

When shooting the Wolf brand ammo, the empty cases would frequently fail to extract, getting stuck in the chamber.  And I mean stuck, as in he had to insert a brass rod down the barrel from the muzzle and hammer the case out.  The rim of the case would be torn, where the extractor had tried to pull it out.  note:  I’ll include the brass rod (3/16 inch, 4.76 mm, a couple of bucks at Home Depot).

I’ve shot a lot of Wolf ammo over the years.  While I wouldn’t trust my life to it, it was always fine for recreational and training shooting.  But not this batch.  The batch of Wolf ammo we bought seems especially problematic; it even causes my FS2000 and Tavor to seize up in a similar manner.

Another friend of mine who also bought a Bushmaster XM-15 in November 2008 had extraction issues with his rifle (not quite the same problem, but I don’t remember the details).

This upper receiver and barrel assembly hasn’t had problems with regular brass-case ammo.


Anyway, my friend recently got another complete upper receiver assembly (with Magpul hand guards in olive drab, so he ended up changing the stock and pistol grip to match), which is why this is for sale.

Before putting this up for sale, I decided to try and quantify the failure rate (and possibly troubleshoot) so I could let any potential buyers know what to expect.  I took this upper, put it on my AR-15 lower, and shot 60 rounds of Wolf, 20 rounds of Prvi Partizan PPU, and another 20 rounds of Wolf:  100 rounds total.  I had zero failures:  zip, nada, zilch.    I have no idea why it was working with Wolf ammo one day, when shooting Wolf ammo been so problematic over the years.

The universe must be mocking me.




PS —


There are several videos on YouTube of folks who had to get a brass rod and hammer out stuck Wolf cases, so it's not just this receiver/barrel assembly.   For example:


https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JCYMbMogWPY  ( 2 min. 13 sec. )
AR15 - Removing Stuck Steel Cased Ammo
The Kgoat Channel
published on Aug 31, 2013
Quick technique to remove steel cased ammo shell stuck/lodged in your barrell


https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eh9A_Aaz28E  ( 1 min. 32 sec. )
remove steel case ammo stuck in ar
ddsig226
published on May 18, 2012
WOLF AMMO STUCK IN AR



From the YouTube comments, there’s also a link to a very detailed report by Lucky Gunner about shooting 40,000 rounds through 4 Bushmaster XM-15s (10,000 rounds per rifle), along with a 2 minute summary video.

- Federal: 10,000 rounds, 0 malfunctions.
- Brown Bear: 10,000 rounds, 9 malfunctions (5 stuck cases, 1
magazine-related failure to feed, 3 failures to fully cycle)
- Wolf: 10,000 rounds, 15 malfunctions (stuck cases)
- Tula: DNF (6,000 rounds in alternate carbine, 3 malfunctions)


http://www.luckygunner.com/labs/brass-vs-steel-cased-ammo/

Brass vs. Steel Cased Ammo – An Epic Torture Test
January 08, 2013

Up for sale is a new unused CenterPoint 4-16x40 rifle scope. It has parallax adjustments from 5 yards to 200 yards with an infinite parallax setting beyond that. It has red and green illumination with 5 brightness settings on each. It can also be used with no illumination which gives the standard black cross hairs. It is a mil dot reticle. This was given to me for my birthday to use on my Mosin Nagant with scout mount. This is a standard eye relief scope so it will not work for me. It will work for anyone who wants a scope mounted in a conventional manner, I however need about 10" of eye relief. This scope gets many great reviews online for a budget scope. It has been tested on all calibers between .22 and .416 Rigby. This scope also features resettable zero turrets that are the finger dial type that don't need tools to adjust. It also has a quick focus eye piece. Includes a set of decent set of rings. The large 40mm objective has a great field of view and is extremely clear. MSRP is $100, asking $60 obo. 

About this item
Adventure Class scopes come standard with adjustable objectives, delivering a parallax-free image, without moving the point of impact. This means, if your target moves, your scope can adjust quickly and accurately at any distance. And their dual illuminated reticles offer a bright, sharp image for those fast-moving, close-in shots. Whether you're shooting at dusk or at dawn, in heavy brush or open field, the Adventure Class will deliver a quick, bright image. Includes weaver-style/picatinny mounting rings and flip-open lens caps.

Features
Adjustable objective from 4 to 16x power
40mm Objective 
Dual illuminated Mil-Dot reticle
One Piece, 1-inch tube
Multi-coated lenses
Bonus: Flip-up lens caps and 1-inch picatinny rings

title: For Sale:  1987 Sea Ray Pachanga 19
postcontent:
1987 Sea Ray Pachanga 19. This particular Sea Ray was built in 1987 and comes with a matching 1987 Calkins roller trailer. The boat has a 19'2" centerline length and has a very comfortable 94" beam (width). The Pachanga series was built by Sea Ray to compete with the Fountain and Formula cigarette boats of the 80's and has developed quite a cult following over the years. It has a deep vee hull with lots of freeboard and a large built in swim platform, as well as a very large space under the bow that is fully carpeted and has a headliner, and is actually large enough for me to take a nap under comfortably.

The boat has a Mercruiser Alpha One outdrive with power trim and tilt, and new bellows and water pump were installed by the previous owner the year before I bought it, as well as new fuel line and fuel fill and vent lines and upper seal kit on the outdrive.

I bought the boat at the beginning of last summer and have installed new OEM switches and circuit breakers, new gas lifts for the engine cover, new outdrive trim and tilt sensors and replaced a bad trim tab solenoid.

Features:

4.3L Vortec engine with roller rockers and lifters (engine is an '06-'08 engine and is not original to the boat)
2bbl carb
47 gallon aluminum fuel tank
Halon automatic fire suppression system
blower
full instrumentation (all gauges and switches work)
compass
trim tabs
through the transom exhaust
built in swim platform and swim ladder
new spark plugs
new tags good through the end of 2016
trailer has newer tires that are in great shape with bearing buddies and LED tail lights

The front two pedestal seats do need to be upholstered, and the boat could certainly benefit from a good waxing. The pictures make it look like the gelcoat has worn through, but that is just a reflection, the paint and gelcoat are good shape. Has a cassette stereo that should be swapped out and speakers installed.

I used it last summer, but with a new baby and a "fixer" house I just don't have time to go to the lake for the forseeable future. I drained and winterized the engine, exhaust manifolds and outdrive and filled with RV antifreeze, and it has been covered in the barn since the fall. With the huge 47 gallon fuel tank it can run all day and the V-6 is economical on fuel. I cruise 30MPH at 3000 RPM. With the long bow and deep vee hull it cuts right through the chop and wake board boat wakes. Neat, rare boat. Asking $1695 OBO.

title: For Sale:  HIGH END AR15 PWS MK116 Mod 0 Complete Upper 5.56 Piston Driven AR
postcontent:
For sale is a Primary Weapons System MK116 Mod 0 Complete Upper.  
It utilizes a long-stroke piston system modeled after the ultra-reliable AK-47.
This thing RUNS.  Have fired somewhere between 600-700 rounds.  Not a single malfunction of any kind, not once.  I've fed it everything from quality brass to cheap steel cased Russian stuff like silver bear.  it Eats Anything you feed it.  It also runs extremely clean, significantly cleaner than DI guns.  This is of course due to the design, gases are not kept in contact with the BCG, rather they are pushed into the piston tube. Upper breaks down exactly how a DI upper would, except there is a piston rod attached to the BCG.  It is the simplest and most reliable piston AR design out there.  All the other piston ARs (I've tried most of them..LWRC Barrett POF LMT Sig etc) operate using short-stroke piston designs which utilize more proprietary parts and result in more metal on metal action, and IMO are more problematic (at least potentially, someday down the road). The other thing I should mention on the topic of other piston guns, is that all the other piston ARs I've tried (while nice) are no where near as light or as well-balanced as the PWS.  Most the other piston ARs are front heavy and/or bulky.  The PWS is as light as a DI and AS well-balanced as a DI.  Weighs in under 7lbs.

 Do your research and you'll find not a single bad review on PWS.  It is not quite as well known a company as say LWRC, but I believe it is due to marketing, not the quality of builds, b/c PWS has an extremely loyal fan base.  I for one am not interested in buying any other rifles outside of the PWS brand.  Only selling b/c I'm tight on cash, otherwise I'd keep it.  If I didn't have another PWS sitting at home I wouldn't even be selling it regardless of cash needs.  You will not be disappointed by this upper I can assure you that.

Asking $1000 OBO

Would sell the entire rifle (complete upper with complete lower) for $1500 OBO,
but would prefer to keep the lower as it has the best buffer tube system on the market.
If you live out of state let me know and I may consider shipping FFLs.

Make an offer.

Thanks for looking

The PMR-30 is a light weight, full size pistol chambered for the flat-shooting .22Magnum cartridge (.22WMR). The PMR-30 operates on a unique hybrid blowback/locked-breech system.
